---
title: Authentication — Google Sign-In on iOS
---
%% Last updated: 2026-05-29
%% Scope: From user tapping "Continue with Google" on iOS to first authenticated API call landing on Fly.
%% Note: Apple Sign-In follows the same shape with expo-apple-authentication + caller-supplied nonce.
%%       Email/password skips steps 2-5 and hits Supabase directly via signInWithPassword.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant App as Mobile app (RN)
    participant SDK as Google native SDK
    participant Safari as iOS ASWebAuthenticationSession
    participant Google as Google OAuth (us-east)
    participant SA as Supabase Auth (Stockholm)
    participant DB as Supabase Postgres (Stockholm)
    participant Fly as Backend API (Fly arn)

    User->>App: Tap "Continue with Google"
    App->>SDK: GoogleSignin.signIn()
    SDK->>Safari: Open accounts.google.com (PKCE + nonce)
    Safari->>Google: GET /authorize
    Google->>User: Pick account, consent
    User->>Google: Submit
    Google-->>Safari: Redirect to custom URL scheme<br/>com.googleusercontent.apps.446154042539-...
    Safari-->>SDK: ID token (JWT signed by Google)
    SDK-->>App: { idToken, user }

    Note over App,SA: ID token now in mobile app memory.<br/>Never logged, never sent to our API directly.

    App->>SA: POST /token<br/>signInWithIdToken({ provider: google, token: idToken })
    SA->>Google: Fetch JWKS (cached)
    Google-->>SA: Public keys
    SA->>SA: Verify signature + audience claim<br/>(audience must match an authorized client ID)

    Note right of SA: Skip nonce checks MUST be ON for iOS:<br/>Google native SDK generates an internal nonce<br/>it does not expose, so caller can not supply one.

    SA->>DB: Upsert auth.users + profiles row
    DB-->>SA: user
    SA-->>App: { access_token (1h), refresh_token (long-lived) }

    App->>App: Store session in SecureStore<br/>(Keychain on iOS, EncryptedSharedPreferences on Android)

    App->>Fly: GET /me<br/>Authorization: Bearer access_token
    Fly->>SA: Fetch JWKS (cached, ~1 ms)
    SA-->>Fly: Public keys
    Fly->>Fly: Verify JWT locally<br/>(no network round-trip per request)
    Fly->>DB: SELECT * FROM profiles WHERE user_id = auth.uid()<br/>(RLS enforces ownership)
    DB-->>Fly: profile row
    Fly-->>App: 200 OK + user profile

    User->>App: Sees authenticated home screen
